detaileddescription.para: Event type emitted by a DTLS protocol object when its state changes.
The event struct is just a plain GG_Event. The event source is the GG_DtlsProtocol object that emits the event.

memberdef.name: GG_DtlsProtocol_Create

detaileddescription.para: Create a new DTLS protocol object

parameterdescription.para: Specifies if the object is a client or server.

Options used to configure the object. When the role is GG_TLS_ROLE_CLIENT, this must be a pointer to a GG_TlsClientOptions structure. When the role is GG_TLS_ROLE_SERVER, this must be a pointer to a GG_TlsServerOptions structure.
Maximum size of the datagrams that may be sent and received.
A timer scheduler used for scheduling retransmission timers.
Pointer to where the object will be returned.

simplesect.para: GG_SUCCESS if the object could be created, or a negative error code.

parameterdescription.para: The object on which this method is invoked.

detaileddescription.para: Start the DTLS handshake. For clients, this will start emitting datagrams to the transport. For servers, this will place the object in a mode where it is waiting for datagrams from the transport.

simplesect.para: GG_SUCCESS if the handshake could be started, or a negative error code.

detaileddescription.para: Reset the DTLS session. NOTE: this will not automatically re-start the handshake. It is up to the caller to subsequently call GG_DtlsProtocol_StartHandshake to start a new handshake.

parameterdescription.para: The object on which this method is invoked.

simplesect.para: GG_SUCCESS if the handshake could be reset, or a negative error code.
